The paper deals with the analysis of a stochastic process on a graph, which suggests that it could belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The process involves probabilities and randomness, which are common themes in Game Theory (cs.GT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of polynomial bounds and randomized approximation schemes suggests that it could also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NE) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) categories.
